OL,5,Ctime
OL,7,FAnthony says he feels the company, who
OL,8,Fsay they have a track record of
OL,9,Fdelivering large-scale public events
OL,10,Facross hundreds of venues, didn't keep
OL,11,Fto their side of the agreement.
OL,13,F"We gave them the car park for free
OL,14,Ffor their customers to park. We've
OL,15,Fnever charged for that car park ever.
OL,16,FThe second night of the event was
OL,17,Fopen, we found out they were charging
OL,18,Fthe customers #4 per car to park when
OL,19,Fthe customers already paid 30 quid for
OL,20,Fa ticket to get in".
